26/10/2009
LUXEMBOURG -- A two-day meeting of the EU foreign ministers begins on Monday (October 26th) in Luxembourg. 
One of topic on the agenda is the current situation in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH), following talks among political leaders there and senior EU and US officials on reforms needed to accelerate the country's European and Euro-Atlantic integration. 
EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn and Swedish Foreign Minister Carl Bildt, whose country currently holds the EU presidency, will brief the bloc's foreign ministers on the negotiation process. 
(RTRS, Fena, Dnevni Avaz - 25/10/09)
